<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bead" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bead,</orth> 1) any small globular body: <emph>with amber bracelets, --s</emph> (== pearls) <cit><quote>and all this knavery,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 4.3.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 3, 58</bibl></cit>. <emph>these crystal --s</emph> (i. e. tears) <bibl n="shak. jn 2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 171</bibl>. <cit><quote>--s of sweat,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 3, 61</bibl></cit>. <emph>--s of sorrow</emph> (tears) <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.284" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 284</bibl>.<lb />2) any thing extremely small: <cit><quote>you b., you acorn,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.330" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 330</bibl></cit>. Hence name of a fairy: <bibl n="shak. wiv 5.5.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. V, 5, 53</bibl> (Ff. <emph>Bede</emph>).
<lb />3) <emph>Beads</emph> == rosary: <bibl n="shak. err 2.2.190" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. II, 2, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.147" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 147</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.3.59" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.162" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 162</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.93" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 93</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>